I apologize but I have to ramble a bit(okay a lot) because I'm confused about something in the film and tbh a bit annoyed as well. I also apologize for my mistakes in the grammar. I hope I didn't mess it up too badlyüôÇ

I never bothered to watch the movie in English before so I didn't notice until now... It's a great film but what the heck did they think they do when they did the German synchro in the original version? I had to repeat it to understand what they were saying and I'm German for god's sake! Also, at least one of the translations is just incorrect and doesn't make sense. In 1:30:somewhat an officer says (according to subtitle) "Time to introduce little Hansel" but what he actually said was: "Zu viele F√ºchse f√ºr euch paar H√ºhner" which would translate to somewhat across the line of: "Too many foxes for you few chicken" and that just doesn't make sense to me? It's done correctly in the German version: "Zeit den kleinen H√§nsel vorzustellen" which is the actual translation for "Time to introduce little Hansel". I mean I'm used to it by now that German often sounds awful when it's spoken in foreign movies and I'm okay with that most of the time. But sometimes it's really annoying! They do have synchros in German for the German parts so why can't they just use them in the original version?

Title: Sherlock Holmes: A Game of Shadows (2011) EXCLUSIVE HD Trailer
Comment: @Cavelcade I don't think it's anyone's fault, and exasperation doesn't equal no respect. I am often exasperated at my best friend but there is no one else I respect more. So I hardly see Watson's "exasperation" at Holmes as a meaning of him not giving a huge respect to Holmes. You don't have to be all nice and kind and gentle to respect someone. And anyways, if someone's trying to interrupt your love life/marriage, you would be exasperated too, but that isn't the same as no respect.

Title: Sherlock Holmes: A Game of Shadows (2011) EXCLUSIVE HD Trailer
Comment: @BetaArtemis They work in tune, but (to be fair, this is probably either Jude Law or the director's fault) Watson seems to be exasperated with Holmes throughout. While this certainly occasionally happened, it was always for a very brief period and was very rare. I'd forgotten what had annoyed me more though, which is the character they seem to be giving Moriarty, even in the first movie. He'd never have met Irene in a carriage, he'd have had a lackey do it. I'm still going to see this, though.

Title: Sherlock Holmes: A Game of Shadows (2011) EXCLUSIVE HD Trailer
Comment: @Cavelcade I still don't see how this one short trailer showed that Holmes didn't respect Watson or Watson didn't respect Holmes, just because they are yelling or bickering doesn't mean there is no trust or respect. A trailer isn't everything and just because they didn't show those "respect" scenes doesn't mean there isn't any. As far as I'm concerned, I have no reason to believe why there isn't respect, they seem to be working in tune just fine.

Title: Sherlock Holmes: A Game of Shadows (2011) EXCLUSIVE HD Trailer
Comment: @BetaArtemis Because above all things, Watson has huge respect for Sherlock Holmes at that stage in their relationship. Certainly at the beginning he was a skeptic but, as their relationship progressed, that's one of the primary feelings that he brings across. The fact is, in this trailer I get no sense of respect. Holmes certainly has a good deal of respect for Watson too, though he's less inclined to show it and in this trailer, again, I get little sense of the respect for his side, either.
